      "content": "you said \"in reality, tariffs are a blunt instrument...\" sounds like you're saying the consumer side of the argument is more fundamentally true than the industry protection side. if they actually help domestic workers and bring manufacturing back, isn't that a more important goal than just keeping prices low for people? why does it seem like the downsides are more \"real\" than the benefits?",
